# TRIGEN-Orchestration Workspace Rules

- Treat this repository as a standalone public VS Code extension project.
- Do not import REI:FA, PROJECT_REI, or private research assumptions into this project.
- Prefer Japanese UI copy first, with concise English copy directly below it.
- Keep the left TRIGEN view focused on agent settings only.
- Keep the right TRIGEN view focused on the 3-agent unified chat only.
- Do not restore dedicated per-agent chat windows.
- Do not expose explicit orchestration mode buttons in the UI; infer the internal route from unified chat context.
- Respect provider boundaries: do not scrape provider webviews, credentials, cookies, or another extension's secret storage.
